                <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.51/12–2845: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Saudi Arabia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eddy</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-01-04T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 4, 1946—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2. Re your 443, December 28. Newly constituted Board of Directors of ExImbank, at
                    first meeting on January 3, approved a $25,000,000 line of credit for Saudi
                    Arabia in accordance with terms of draft agreement previously sent you by air
                    pouch and summarized in Depts 368, December 20. Exact text of proposed agreement
                    will be supplied soon with instructions concerning translations, signatures, et
                    cetera.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
